TERA MAI TE TIARE. Freshwater pearls, Ei Pupu shells from French Polynesia, Swarovski Crystals, Black Onyx & Glass Beads.  TOMORROW!!

Tera Mai Te Tiare. This woven necklace took about a week from start to finish. It is one of the most laborious work I have ever done. Long hours of drawing and beading freshwater pearls ( yes! those teeny tiny white bead like materials are fresh water pearls too) and it was no joke getting them to thread. We often look at beading from a very “arts and crafts” lens which I find to be very heartbreaking because only a beader knows how tedious and time consuming this work is to not be seen in the same regard as other “crafts”. The necklace uses three shapes of fresh water pearls, tiny shells from French Polynesia, Swarovski crystals, Black Onyx and pyrite and glass beads along with brass enclosure and clasps with laser engraved logo. Necklace is available in store online along with other offerings and more coming soon 🌺🐚

Une Baleine : Fresh water pearls, Black Pyrite, Pupu Niau shells from French Polynesia and Glass Beads. Brass enclosure with laser engraved logo. Inspired by the nature and way of life in French Polynesia, each necklace depicts a specific object or living being that make the landscape of the South Pacific 🩵🐋🩵 ps: the neurally occurring irregular sizing of the pearls makes the jewels have a very organic lengths of the tassels at times.

A little note on shells. Shells are trending this summer and I’m guessing will continue to until next year or so. Granted that nature will always be in style and we will continue to take from her however I  would like to say that a lot of shells that are being sold most likely do not have a source credited nor are they sustainably procured. I do not mean to judge anyone for partaking in purchasing or selling of shell jewels but even luxury companies are not taking responsibility of the fact that these were once living beings or their homes. They come from the ocean and we must be mindful of that. Commercial/ industrial grade fishing and procuring of shells where neither the environment nor the animals in question are considered are detrimental for the ecosystem. Small scale sellers who depend on their surroundings for their livelihood is possibly the best way to go about this. Ofocurse it’s impossible to be 100% ethical but we can definitely consume mindfully. Pictured are just a fraction of shells that I collected ( naturally beached) from the South Pacific 🐚

Roses are red @violette_fr is Dieu Bleu 💙 I have known Violette’s incredible work for a few years. To see her explore her art background and come up with this new shade that is forever etched in almost every artist’s memory, Yves Klein Blue, means a lot more because now it’s found a place on our bodies. Congratulation @violette_fr and I am so happy to be partnering / painting with you. Thank you

Last week I had the incredible honor of touring @steinwayandsons factory in Astoria, Queens. We spent about 2-3 hours touring the space and seeing the entire process of making these handmade pianos from start to finish by some of the most skilled artists and builders. I got to goof around and play with some of the most incredible grand piano the world has to offer ( i don’t play the piano, yet 🙃) but the whole experience was one of the best things i’ve done in New York in a long time. Congratulations to @steinwayandsons for your Mickey piano collaboration with @disney . I had the best time ( as you can tell when i say WOW). Thank you @kcdworldwide for this amazing experience

I’ve been playing around on my computer quite a bit. Although my background in music is predominantly singing + playing the guitar, this year has been crucial in reconnecting to myself and remembering what I love deeply and finding myself through it again. The Death Card is where I learn, play and grow: think of it like a playground. I have three songs to share as of now, my first three ever in a completely new medium. Here’s to feeling very naked and very vulnerable 🥂  Thank you @vishalnayakmusic for mixing these tracks. You can find The Death Card on Spotify.
